      "writtenOn": "2020-10-07T15:39:35Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "vector\u003cbool\u003e actually lacks a lot of basics that we would want, e.g. there\u0027s no real equivalent to `forEachSetIndex` or `forEachUnsetIndex`. It tries so hard to pretend it\u0027s a vector that it doesn\u0027t support doing anything in bulk 32/64-bits at a time (e.g. no way to XOR one vector\u003cbool\u003e against another other than one bit at a time). It doesn\u0027t even seem to include a `data()` method to expose the underlying bits.",
      "parentUuid": "bce59bf4_989c5169",
      "revId": "851eeffc6f531b4be875d32358f4c78a3d81ac0f",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
    {
