      "writtenOn": "2020-10-07T15:44:28Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yeah, I\u0027m kinda against this. The point of SkBitSet was to be like std::bitset but with the flexibility of N being a runtime thing (which is fairly straight forward to layer on top). If you want to start resizing and whatnot, that\u0027s what std::vector\u003cbool\u003e is for. libc++ actually does optimize std::find_* for std::vector\u003cbool\u003e to do the same thing we do here (though notably libstdc++ and msvc STL do not).",
      "parentUuid": "bce59bf4_989c5169",
      "revId": "851eeffc6f531b4be875d32358f4c78a3d81ac0f",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": false,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "709a417f_67a6c0ad",
        "filename": "/PATCHSET_LEVEL",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
